The paper focuses on deep generative models for images, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of experimental methods from cognitive psychology suggests a potential overlap with neural networks and neuroscience (cs.NE), while the investigation of how models generate novel attributes and their combinations suggests a potential overlap with natural language processing (cs.CL).
